{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_39","type":"agent_message","text":"The current picture is that Jersey’s own service/provider discovery is dragging in `MimeMultipartProvider` as a built-in reader/writer, not the test code. I’m checking whether that constructor is failing because multipart support depends on optional mail classes; if so, this is a native-incompatible provider-discovery path and the right fix is to keep the test on the public HTTP path while preventing that provider from being exercised."}}
